0in%20consulting.%3Cp%3EVarun%20Kulkarni%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EVarun%20Kulkarni%20transitioned%20from%20consulting%20to%20a%20senior%20product%20manager%20role%20at%20Cisco.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20spent%20about%20eight%20months%20preparing%20for%20the%20shift%20in%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20tailored%20his%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20highlight%20skills%20that%20apply%20to%20tech%20more%20than%20they%20do%20to%20consulting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EVarun%20Kulkarni%20was%20five%20years%20into%20his%20consulting%20role%20at%20Deloitte%20when%20he%20realized%20he%20wanted%20a%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%202022%2C%20and%20he%20had%20started%20getting%20involved%20in%20artificial%20intelligence-related%20projects%20at%20the%20company.%20He%20knew%20he%20could%20do%20more%20with%20his%20expertise%20and%20interest%20in%20tech%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20really%20started%20coming%20into%20play%20and%20I%20started%20seeing%20how%20AI%20products%20really%20made%20a%20bigger%20impact%20in%20the%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20Tech%2C%20which%20creates%20products%20that%20reach%20millions%20of%20global%20users%2C%20seemed%20like%20the%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20most%20skills%20from%20consulting%20seemed%20transferable%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-job-resume-tips-machine-learning-specialist-career-switch-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20the%20jump%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20Kulkarni%20about%20eight%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20spent%20three%20months%20preparing%20for%20tech%20interviews%2C%20which%20included%20taking%20higher%20product%20usage%20into%20account%20and%20unlearning%20aspects%20of%20consulting%20such%20as%20moving%20quickly.%20Next%2C%20he%20spent%20about%20two%20months%20cold-emailing%20and%20networking%20with%20people%20who%20had%20made%20a%20similar%20move%20from%20consulting%20to%20tech.%20He%20alloc