ssinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hololens-like-army-device-gets-poor-marks-from-soldiers-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIVAS%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20whittled%20down%2C%20with%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20business%20and%20engineering%20brainpower%20moving%20on%20to%20other%20projects%2C%20the%20people%20said.%20They%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20discussing%20private%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20no%20longer%20investing%20in%20major%20innovative%20improvements%20to%20the%20IVAS%20device%20and%20is%20instead%20focusing%20on%20smaller%2C%20iterative%20updates%20requested%20by%20the%20military.%20It's%20also%20having%20the%20military%20pay%20for%20these%20updates%2C%20according%20to%20the%20people%20familiar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20people%20said%20the%20changes%20signal%20the%20%26quot%3Bdeath%20knell%26quot%3B%20for%20Microsoft's%20involvement%20in%20IVAS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20to%20invest%20in%20mixed%20reality%20opportunities%20with%20first-party%20software%20solutions%20and%20services%2C%20partnering%20with%20the%20broader%20mobile%20phone%20and%20mixed%20reality%20hardware%20ecosystem%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20addition%2C%20we%20remain%20fully%20committed%20to%20the%20IVAS%20program%20with%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Defense%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22343f4684-f91d-4ad5-8f74-1d591c42e5b8%5C%22%3EHoloLens%20history%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft's%20HoloLens%20device%20was%20unveiled%20in%202015.%20The%20goggles%20allow%20the%20wearer%20to%20see%20digital%20information%20overlaid%20on%20their%20view%20of%20the%20physical%20world%2C%20displaying%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20an%20instruction%20manual%20that%20a%20technician%20can%20glance%20at%20while%20repairing%20an%20appliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20previous%20ill-fated%20efforts%20to%20sell%20mixed-%20and%20augmented-reality%20devices%20to%20consumers%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-google-glass-insight%2Fgoogle-glass-future-clouded-as-some-early-believers-lose-faith-idUSKCN0IY18E20141114%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGoogle%20Glass%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Microsoft%20positioned%20HoloLens%20as%20a%20product%20for%20businesses%20and%20other%20large%20organizations.%20It%20invested%20heavily%20in%20the%20experimental%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20patience%20began%20to%20wane%20as%20the%20product%20failed%20to%20achieve%20commercial%20success.%20In%202022%2C%20Microsoft%20scrapped%20plans%20for%20a%20third%20version%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hololens-3-metaverse-mixed-reality-strategy-confusion-rivalries-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edevice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20BI%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20original%20HoloLens%20had%20sold%20between%2040%2C000%20and%2060%2C000%20units%20since%20it%20launched%20in%202016.%20At%20the%20high%20end%2C%20that%20would%20be%20%24210%20million%20in%20revenue%2C%20based%20on%20the%20device's%20%243%2C500-plus%20sticker%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220313a5bf-4373-41d1-af92-aa886a4c2621%5C%22%3EBig%20losses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20people%20who%20spoke%20with%20BI%2C%20who%20has%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20project's%20financials%2C%20said%20it%20had%20been%20burning%20through%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20recent%20years.%20After%20several%20years%2C%20Microsoft%20began%20to%20question%20whether%20the%20heavy%20spending%20would%20ever%20pay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20person%20now%20estimates%20that%20HoloLens%20has%20lost%20a%20total%20of%20more%20than%20%245%20billion%20over%20the%20years.%20The%20other%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20put%20total%20losses%20at%20multiple%20billions%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20HoloLens%20co-creator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-toxic-culture-ceo-satya-nadella-sexual-harassment-pay-disparity-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlex%20Kipman%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%20Microsoft%20following%20BI's%20report%20on%20allegations%20that%20he%20behaved%20inappropriately%20toward%20some%20female%20employees.%20Kipman%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20on%20BI's%20report%20at%20the%20time.%20Microsoft%20started%20to%20dismantle%20the%20team%20at%20that%20time%2C%20initially%20through%20a%20reorganization%2C%20according%20to%20an%20email%20viewed%20by%20BI%2C%20and%20later%20through%20layoffs.%20Many%20of%20the%20mixed-reality%20team's%20leaders%20have%20left%20for%20other%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%2010-year%20IVAS%20contract%20was%20expected%20to%20be%20worth%20as%20much%20as%20%2422%20billion%2C%20it%20suffered%20delays%20and%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-hololens-3-metaverse-mixed-reality-strategy-confusion-rivalries-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eplagued%20by%20quality%20and%20performance%20problems%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20devices%20would%20have%20gotten%20us%20killed%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20tester%20said%20after%20a%202022%20test%20of%20Microsoft's%20device%20for%20the%20military%2C%20in%20an%20excerpt%20of%20an%20Army%20report%20dictated%20to%20BI.%20That%20tester%20was%20referring%20to%20the%20light%20generated%20by%20the%20goggles%20when%20they're%20active%2C%20which%20could%20alert%20enemy%20fighters%20to%20soldiers'%20locations.%20Other%20criticisms%20at%20the%20time%20included%20that%20the%20device%20was%20bulky%20enough%20to%20restrict%20moment%20and%20limited%20soldiers'%20peripheral%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223bec141c-7184-4b90-8b68-4f1d960a12e5%5C%22%3EAI