%20as%20a%20dreamer%20and%20visionary%20who%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20car%20that%20would%20keep%20the%20common%20man%20riding%20a%20two-wheeler%20%26quot%3Bout%20of%20the%20rain%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20car%20would%20be%20built%20in%20Bengal's%20Singur%20was%20a%20surprise%20announcement%2C%20Ms%20Radia%20told%20NDTV%20-%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20not%20told%20what%20would%20be%20the%20site.%20We%20were%20really%20surprised%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERatan%20Tata%2C%20she%20said%2C%20chose%20Bengal%20because%20he%20felt%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20state%20needed%20industrialisation.%20He%20chose%20Singur%2C%20because%20that%20was%20the%20seat%20of%20a%20legislator%20from%20the%20Opposition%20--%20Rabindranath%20Bhattacharya%20of%20Trinamool%20Congress.%20Because%20%26quot%3Bhe%20always%20wanted%20to%20take%20everybody%20along%20with%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Ms%20Radia%2C%20a%20close%20friend%20and%20confidante%20of%20the%20industrialist%20and%20philanthropist%20who%20died%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20natural%20for%20him.%20Why%20shouldn't%20it%20be%20Singur%3F%20He%20was%20for%20development%2C%20not%20to%20play%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Radia%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20the%20plan%20worked%2C%20it%20would%20have%20brought%20unprecedented%20development%20-%20the%20way%20it%20did%20in%20Gujarat's%20Sanand%2C%20where%20the%20project%20shifted%20after%20the%20Opposition%20by%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20who%20rode%20to%20power%20in%202011%20on%20the%20back%20of%20that%20campaign.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20road%20from%20Kolkata%20to%20Singur%20would%20have%20developed%20hugely.%20As%20it%20happened%20in%20Sanad....%20a%20great%20fillip.%20Today%20Sanand%20is%20like%20Gurgaon%2C'%20she%20said%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20opposition%20to%20the%20project%20at%20the%20time%20was%20purely%20political.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20not%20about%20the%20Nano%2C%20Ratan%2C%20or%20the%20Tatas%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Radia%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Left%20Front%20government%20had%20won%20the%202006%C2%A0state%20assembly%20election%20on%20the%20promise%20of%20industrialization%2C%20development%20and%20jobs.%20The%20Nano%20project%20-%20announced%20by%20then%20Chief%20Minister%20Buddhadeb%20Bhattacharjee%20that%20May%20--%20was%20seen%20as%20the%20vanguard%20of%20that%20change.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20of%20the%20997%20acres%20acquired%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%20347%20acres%20became%20disputed.%20The%20farmers%20found%20a%20champion%20in%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20who%20held%20a%2026-day%20hunger%20strike%20that%20drew%20attention%20across%20the%20country%20and%20ultimately%20changed%20the%20course%20of%20Bengal's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENano%20ultimately%20went%20to%20Gujarat%2C%20then%20helmed%20by%20Narendra%20Modi.%20%26quot%3BWe%20visited%20many%20states%20--%20Punjab%2C%20Karnataka%20and%20Uttarakhand%20-%20after%20getting%20invitations.%20Then%20we%20got%20the%20invitation%20from%20Gujarat.%20Modi%20was%20there%20and%20there%20were%20Tata%20plants%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20he%20wanted%20to%20move%20to%20a%20state%20which%20is%20already%20industrialized%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Radia%20told%20NDTV.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETata%20Nano%20was%20discontinued%20by%20the%20company%20in%202020%20after%20poor%20public%20response.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20emotional%20note%20on%20Instagram%20two%20years%20later%2C%20Ratan%20Tata%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20really%20motivated%20me%2C%20and%20sparked%20a%20desire%20to%20produce%20such%20a%20vehicle%2C%20was%20constantly%20seeing%20Indian%20families%20on%20scooters%2C%20maybe%20the%20child%20sandwiched%20between%20the%20mother%20and%20father%2C%20riding%20to%20wherever%20they%20were%20going%2C%20often%20on%20slippery%20roads.%20One%20of%20the%20benefits%20of%20being%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Architecture%2C%20it%20had%20taught%20me%20to%20doodle%20when%20I%20was%20free.%20At%20first%20we%20were%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20make%20two%20wheelers%20safer%2C%20the%20doodles%20became%20four%20wheels%2C%20no%20windows%2C%20no%20doors%2C%20just%20a%20basic%20dune%20buggy.%20But%20I%20finally%20decided%20it%20should%20be%20a%20car.%20The%20Nano%2C%20was%20always%20meant%20for%20all%20our%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728923880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fqq81hep_niira-radia_625x300_14_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fniira-radia-explains-why-ratan-tata-chose-singur-for-nano-factory-6788701%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20decision%20to%20build%20Nano%2C%20the%20Rs%201%20lakh%20car%2C%20in%20Bengal's%20Singur%2C%20had%20taken%20Ratan%20Tata's%20team%20by%20surprise%2C%20as%20did%20the%20price%20point%20of%20the%20car%2C%20Niira%20Radia%20told%20NDTV.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fniira-radia-explains-why-ratan-tata-chose-singur-for-nano-factory-6788701%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Trump%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20care%20about%20anyone%20but%20himself%E2%80%99%3A%20Supporters%20left%20stranded%20in%2093%C2%B0F%20heat%20after%20rally%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728922986000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114224905%2Cimgsize-1426666.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-doesnt-care-about-anyone-but-himself-supporters-left-stranded-in-93f-heat-after-rally%2Farticleshow%2F114224673.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F114224673.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ESupporters%20were%20left%20stranded%20for%20hours%20in%2093%C2%B0F%20heat%20after%20a%20Donald%20Trump%20rally%20in%20Coachella%20Valley.%20The%20event%20faced%20multiple%20issues%2C%20including%20a%20suspected%20assassination%20attempt%20and%20inadequate%20transportation%20arrangements.%20Despite%20Trump's%20claim%20of%20100%2C000%20attendees%2C%20the%20permit%20allowed%20only%2015%2C000.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-doesnt-care-about-anyone-but-himself-supporters-left-stranded-in-93f-heat-after-rally%2Farticleshow%2F114224673.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-doesnt-care-about-anyone-but-himself-supporters-left-stranded-in-93f-heat-after-rally%2Famp_articleshow%2F114224673.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-doesnt-care-about-anyone-but-himself-supporters-left-stranded-in-93f-heat-after-rally%2Famp_articleshow%2F114224673.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NASA's%20Europa%20Clipper%20Probe%20Lifts%20Off%20For%20Jupiter's%20Icy%20Moon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENASA%20launched%20a%20spacecraft%20from%20Florida%20on%20Monday%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20examine%20whether%20Jupiter's%20moon%20Europa%20has%20conditions%20suitable%20to%20support%20life%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20the%20large%20subsurface%20ocean%20believed%20to%20be%20lurking%20beneath%20its%20thick%20outer%20shell%20of%20ice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20space%20agency's%20Europa%20Clipper%20spacecraft%20blasted%20off%20from%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20in%20Cape%20Canaveral%20on%20a%20SpaceX%20Falcon%20Heavy%20rocket%20under%20sunny%20skies.%20The%20robotic%20solar-powered%20probe%20is%20due%20to%20enter%20orbit%20around%20Jupiter%20in%202030%20after%20journeying%20about%201.8%20billion%20miles%20(2.9%20billion%20km)%20in%205-1%2F2%20years.%20The%20launch%20had%20been%20planned%20for%20last%20week%20but%20was%20put%20off%20because%20of%20Hurricane%20Milton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20largest%20spacecraft%20NASA%20has%20built%20for%20a%20planetary%20mission%2C%20at%20about%20100%20feet%20(30.5%20meters)%20long%20and%20about%2058%20feet%20(17.6%20meters)%20wide%20with%20its%20antennas%20and%20solar%20arrays%20fully%20deployed%20-%20bigger%20than%20a%20basketball%20court%20-%20while%20weighing%20approximately%2013%2C000%20pounds%20(6%2C000%20kg).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Europa%2C%20the%20fourth-largest%20of%20Jupiter's%2095%20officially%20recognized%20moons%2C%20is%20just%20a%20quarter%20of%20Earth's%20diameter%2C%20its%20vast%20global%20ocean%20of%20salty%20liquid%20water%20may%20contain%20twice%20the%20water%20in%20Earth's%20oceans.%20Earth's%20oceans%20are%20thought%20to%20have%20been%20the%20birthplace%20of%20life%20on%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEuropa%2C%20whose%20diameter%20of%20roughly%201%2C940%20miles%20(3%2C100%20km)%20is%20approximately%2090%25%20that%20of%20our%20moon%2C%20has%20been%20viewed%20as%20a%20potential%20habitat%20for%20life%20beyond%20Earth%20in%20our%20solar%20system.%20Its%20icy%20shell%20is%20believed%20to%20be%2010-15%20miles%20(15-25%20km)%20thick%2C%20sitting%20atop%20an%20ocean%2040-100%20miles%20(60-150%20km)%20deep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20Associate%20Administrator%20Jim%20Free%20told%20a%20prelaunch%20briefing%20on%20Sunday%20that%20Europa%20boasts%20one%20of%20the%20most%20promising%20environments%20for%20potential%20habitability%20in%20our%20solar%20system%2C%20beyond%20Earth%2C%20though%20he%20noted%20that%20this%20mission%20will%20not%20be%20a%20search%20for%20any%20actual%20living%20organisms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20discover%20on%20Europa%2C%26quot%3B%20Free%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwill%20have%20profound%20implications%20for%20the%20study%20of%20astrobiology%20and%20how%20we%20view%20our%20place%20in%20the%20universe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScientists%20believe%20Europa%20has%20suitable%20conditions%20below%20its%20icy%20surface%20to%20support%20life.%20Its%20conditions%20are%20water%2C%20energy%2C%20chemistry%20and%20stability%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sandra%20Connelly%2C%20deputy%20associate%20administrator%20of%20NASA's%20science%20mission%20directorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20mission%2C%20objectives%20are%20measuring%20the%20internal%20ocean%20and%20the%20layer%20of%20ice%20above%20it%2C%20mapping%20the%20moon's%20surface%20composition%2C%20and%20hunting%20for%20plumes%20of%20water%20vapour%20that%20may%20be%20venting%20from%20Europa's%20icy%20crust.%20The%20plan%20is%20for%20Europa%20Clipper%20starting%20in%202031%20to%20conduct%2049%20close%20flybys%20of%20Europa%20over%20three%20years%2C%20coming%20as%20close%20as%2016%20miles%20(25%20kilometers)%20to%20the%20moon's%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEuropa%20Clipper%20will%20be%20operating%20in%20an%20intense%20radiation%20environment%20around%20Jupiter%2C%20our%20solar%20system's%20biggest%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJupiter%20is%20enveloped%20by%20a%20magnetic%20field%20about%2020%2C000%20times%20stronger%20than%20Earth's.%20This%20magnetic%20field%20spins%2C%20capturing%20and%20accelerating%20charged%20particles%20and%20creating%20radiation%20that%20could%20harm%20spacecraft.%20NASA%20fashioned%20a%20vault%20made%20of%20titanium%20and%20aluminium%20inside%20the%20Europa%20Clipper%20to%20protect%20its%20sensitive%20electronics%20from%20this%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20Europa%20Clipper%20mission's%20main%20challenges%20is%20delivering%20a%20spacecraft%20hardy%20enough%20to%20withstand%20the%20pummeling%20of%20radiation%20from%20Jupiter%20but%20also%20sensitive%20enough%20to%20gather%20the%20measurements%20needed%20to%20investigate%20Europa's%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Connelly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20said%20Europa%20Clipper%20is%20loaded%20with%20more%20than%206%2C060%20pounds%20(2%2C750%20kg)%20of%20propellant%20to%20get%20it%20to%20Jupiter.%20For%20the%20launch%2C%20the%20spacecraft%20was%20placed%20inside%20the%20protective%20nose%20cone%20atop%20the%20rocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spacecraft%20will%20not%20take%20a%20straight%20path%20to%20Jupiter.%20Instead%2C%20it%20is%20due%20to%20fly%20by%20Mars%2C%20then%20back%20by%20Earth%2C%20using%20the%20gravity%20of%20each%20planet%20to%20increase%20its%20momentum%20like%20a%20slingshot.%20Its%20expansive%20solar%20arrays%2C%20which%20were%20folded%20up%20for%20the%20launch%2C%20will%20gather%20sunlight%20for%20powering%20the%20spacecraft's%20nine%20scientific%20instruments%20as%20well%20as%20its%20electronics%20and%20other%20subsystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728922980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2F8gi91gn_nasa-europa-clipper_625x300_14_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnasas-europa-clipper-probe-lifts-off-for-jupiters-icy-moon-6789211%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22NASA%20launched%20a%20spacecraft%20from%20Florida%20on%20Monday%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20examine%20whether%20Jupiter's%20moon%20Europa%20has%20conditions%20suitable%20to%20support%20life%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20the%20large%20subsurface%20ocean%20believed%20to%20be%20lurking%20beneath%20its%20thick%20outer%20shell%20of%20ice.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnasas-europa-clipper-probe-lifts-off-for-jupiters-icy-moon-6789211%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Spacecraft%20blasts%20off%20to%20hunt%20alien%20life%20on%20a%20distant%20moon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728922076000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_ne