%80%9CThe%20newly-married%20girl%20had%20been%20bitten%20by%20a%20cobra%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20found%20out.%20%E2%80%9CThough%20anti-venom%20was%20available%2C%20no%20one%20was%20ready%20to%20administer%20it%20to%20her%20while%20she%20was%20menstruating.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20snake%20bite%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20caused%20her%20death%3B%20a%20venomous%20ethos%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20Dr%20Rani%20unearthed%20the%20regressive%20interpretations%20of%20traditions%20that%20prevailed%20in%20Gadchiroli%2C%20the%20more%20aghast%20she%20was%20left.%20Ironically%2C%20antiquated%20concepts%20like%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekurma%20ghar%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewere%20revered.%20As%20she%20learnt%2C%20the%20edgy%20living%20setup%20could%20accommodate%20three%20to%20four%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F140332%2Fpune-college-students-crowdfund-sanitary-napkins%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emenstruating%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20time.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20women%20were%20supposed%20to%20cook%20for%20themselves%20while%20sometimes%20their%20family%20members%20would%20bring%20them%20food.%20But%20they%20had%20to%20leave%20it%20outside%20the%20hut.%E2%80%9D%20For%20the%20entire%20duration%20of%20the%20menstrual%20exile%2C%20the%20woman%20was%20not%20to%20be%20touched.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20antiquated%20kurma%20ghar%20concept%20involves%20women%20living%20in%20a%20mud%20hut%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20their%20menstrual%20cycle%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1-1728467626-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-369358%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20antiquated%20%3Cem%3Ekurma%20ghar%3C%2Fem%3E%20concept%20involves%20women%20living%20in%20a%20mud%20hut%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20their%20menstrual%20cycle.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20hut%2C%20their%20stock%20of%20period%20cloths%20was%20bait%20for%20lizards%20and%20mice.%20And%20god%20forbid%20the%20women%20run%20out%20of%20pads%2C%20they%20were%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20nature.%20Sometimes%20%3Cem%3Emahua%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20tropical%20Indian%20tree)%20leaves%20covered%20in%20paddy%20chaff%20served%20the%20purpose%3B%20other%20times%20banana%20leaves%20helped%20soak%20the%20blood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20really%20amused%20Dr%20Rani%20was%20the%20fervour%20with%20which%20the%20women%20regarded%20the%20system.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20told%20me%20that%20they%20liked%20the%20days%20they%20spent%20at%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekurma%20ghar%3C%2Fem%3E%20because%20it%20was%20a%20chance%20to%20rest.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20opportunities%20they%20had%20to%20go%20to%20the%20forests%20and%20chat%20with%20their%20friends%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%20While%20some%20women%20were%20fond%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekurma%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebecause%20of%20its%20perks%2C%20others%20feared%20divine%20retribution%20if%20they%20defied%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%20aware%20of%20how%20futile%20it%20would%20prove%20to%20uproot%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F135175%2Ftamil-nadu-sanitary-napkin-incinerators-government-schools-promoting-menstrual-hygiene%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewell-entrenched%20custom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dr%20Rani%20and%20her%20husband%20Dr%20Abhay%20Bang%20(74)%20decided%20to%20revamp%20it%20instead.%20With%20intervention%20from%20the%20Mukul%20Madhav%20Foundation%2C%20the%20Padma%20Shri%20couple%20built%20new%20versions%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekurma%20ghar%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecomplete%20with%20modern%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20Johns%20Hopkins%20to%20Gadchiroli%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20quick%20scan%20of%20the%20couple%E2%80%99s%20achievement%20list%20leaves%20me%20in%20a%20dilemma.%20It%20boasts%2072%20individual%20accolades%20of%20national%20and%20international%20repute%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20%E2%80%98Maharashtra%20Bhushan%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20highest%20civilian%20award%20conferred%20by%20the%20State%20Government%20of%20Maharashtra%3B%20the%20first%20ever%20Distinguished%20Alumnus%20Award%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20International%20Health%2C%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%3B%20the%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20Award%3B%20the%20ICMR%20award%3B%20a%20shortlist%20as%20%E2%80%98Global%20Health%20Heroes%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20TIME%20Magazine%20(2005)%3B%20and%20%E2%80%98Public%20Health%20Champion%E2%80%99%20by%20WHO%20(2016).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20effort%20of%20Dr%20Rani%20and%20Dr%20Abhay%20%E2%80%94%20ex-chairman%20of%20the%20Expert%20Committee%20for%20Tribal%20Health%2C%20appointed%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20to%20frame%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F190299%2Fmaharashtra-doctor-couple-hospital-tribal-community-inspiring-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etribal%20health%20policy%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20recommend%20the%20design%20of%20tribal%20healthcare%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20directed%20towards%20improving%20healthcare%20access%20in%20Gadchiroli.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1728467702.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Rani%20and%20Dr%20Abhay%20Bang%20are%20co-founders%20of%20SEARCH%20(Society%20for%20Education%2C%20Action%20and%20Research%20in%20Community%20Health)%20and%20have%20spent%20three%20decades%20working%20with%20tribal%20communities%20in%20Gadchiroli%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1728467702.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1728467702-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1728467702-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1728467702-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-1728467702-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-369361%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Rani%20and%20Dr%20Abhay%20Bang%20are%20co-founders%20of%20SEARCH%20(Society%20for%20Education%2C%20Action%20and%20Research%20in%20Community%20Health)%20and%20have%20spent%20three%20decades%20working%20with%20tribal%20communities%20in%20Gadchiroli%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20couple%20isn%E2%80%99t%20lauded%20simply%20for%20their%20inventive%20take%20on%20tribal%20healthcare%2C%20but%20also%20their%20culturally%20appropriate%20approaches.%20In%20a%20region%20where%20language%2C%20culture%20barriers%2C%20and%20geographic%20inaccessibility%20pose%20significant%20challenges%2C%20and%20illness%20is%20often%20understood%20through%20spiritual%20beliefs%20and%20traditional%20healing%20practices%2C%20introducing%20modern%20medicine%20required%20thoughtful%20and%20respectful%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20tribes%E2%80%99%20reluctance%20melted%20into%20gratitude%2C%20the%20Bangs%20knew%20they%20were%20on%20the%20right%20path.%20Thirty-nine%20years%20ago%2C%20fresh%20out%20of%20the%20premier%20Johns%20Hopkins%2C%20they%20stood%20at%20the%20precipice%20of%20a%20sea%20of%20opportunities%2C%20each%20more%20lucrative%20than%20the%20other.%20But%2C%20an%20inner%20voice%20guided%20their%20next%20step%20%E2%80%94%20research%20is%20fruitful%20in%20areas%20where%20problems%20exist%2C%20not%20where%20facilities%20are%20ample.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20formed%20the%20backbone%20of%20their%20decision%20to%20head%20to%20the%20naxal-hit%2C%20Maoist%20Gadchiroli%20in%20Maharashtra.%20And%20their%20arrival%20was%20interpreted%20as%20a%20blessing.%20Since%20the%20outset%2C%20the%20couple%20has%20attempted%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F338010%2Fkerala-startup-mykare-building-uber-of-healthcare-for-surgeries%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eachieve%20health%20equity%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20relegating%20reductive%20healthcare%20to%20the%20boot%20and%20bringing%20in%20scientific%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20preliminary%20OPD%20(Out%20Patient%20Department)%20from%20which%20Dr%20Abhay%20and%20Dr%20Rani%20Bhang%20operated%20in%20Gadchiroli%20to%20treat%20tribal%20communities%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-369362%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20preliminary%20OPD%20(Out%20Patient%20Department)%20from%20which%20Dr%20Abhay%20and%20Dr%20Rani%20Bang%20operated%20in%20Gadchiroli%20to%20treat%20tribal%20communities.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tribal%20pockets%20across%20India%2C%20high%20infant%20mortality%20rates%20(IMR)%20continue%20to%20perplex%20authorities%3B%20one%20of%20the%20many%20pressing%20issues.%20Studies%20suggest%20that%20over%2089%20percent%20of%20tribal%20women%20have%20anaemia%2C%20while%20only%2070.1%20per%20cent%20of%20tribal%20women%20deliver%20in%20an%20institution.%20Meanwhile%2C%20children%20from%20tribal%20communities%20were%20found%20to%20be%20almost%20one%20and%20a%20half%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20underweight%20than%20children%20from%20other%20communities.%20This%20owes%20to%20malnourished%20expectant%20mothers%2C%20a%20study%20found%2C%20whose%20findings%20revealed%20that%20only%2025%20percent%20of%20pregnant%20and%20lactating%20tribal%20women%20had%20adequate%20protein%20and%20calorie%20intake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20biggest%20killer%20is%20misinformation%2C%20Dr%20Rani%20remarked%20through%20her%20years%20of%20work%20with%20women%20in%20Gadchiroli.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20four%20major%20issues%20that%20I%20have%20seen%20women%20here%20face%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F143287%2Fup-menstruation-padman-school%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emenstrual%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reproductive%20tract%20infections%20that%20are%20manifested%20in%20the%20form%20of%20white%20discharge%2C%20uterine%20cancers%2C%20and%20infertility%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Rani%20shares.%20She%20spotlights%20the%20gaps%20and%20potential%20solutions%20that%20will%20better%20healthcare%20outcomes%20in%20tribal%20belts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAddress%20the%20gap%20in%20knowledge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMisinformation%20is%20benign%20until%20it%E2%80%99s%20not.%20As%20Dr%20Rani%20discovered%2C%20the%20cultural%20chasms%20of%20health%20are%20deep-rooted.%20Her%20conversations%20with%20women%20in%20Gadchiroli%20revealed%20that%20many%20of%20them%20consider%20%E2%80%98heavy%20menstruation%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20that%20most%20doctors%20would%20term%20%E2%80%98dangerous%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20healthy%20physiology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Rani%20Bhang%20is%20an%20MD%20in%20obstetrics%20and%20gynaecology%20and%20specialises%20in%20women's%20health%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-369365%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Rani%20Bang%20is%20an%20MD%20in%20obstetrics%20and%20gynaecology%20and%20specialises%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20health.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20their%20opinion%2C%20scanty%20or%20normal%20menstruation%20indicates%20that%20the%20blood%20is%20collecting%20in%20the%20uterus%2C%20forming%20lumps%2C%20and%20will%20eventually%20impinge%20on%20their%20vital%20organs%20and%20cause%20death.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20lack%20of%20proper%20diagnoses%20extends%20to%20children%E2%80%99s%20healthcare%20as%20well%2C%20she%20figured.%20%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20when%20we%20started%20working%20in%20Gadchiroli%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F116337%2Fgood-news-india-averted-million-child-deaths-since-2005%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einfant%20mortality%3C%2Fa%3E%20rate%20was%20121%20per%201%2C000%20(indicating%20that%20121%20out%20of%201%2C000%20children%20would%20die%20before%20reaching%20the%20first%20year%20of%20life).%20The%20number%20one%20cause%20was%20childhood%20pneumonia.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20she%20along%20with%20Dr%20Abhay%20trained%20the%20village%20health%20workers%20to%20diagnose%20and%20treat%20the%20condition.%20This%20significantly%20reduced%20the%20infant%20mortality%20rate%20by%2060%20percent.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20model%20was%20accepted%20by%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%2C%20UNICEF%20and%20all%20the%20international%20organisations%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Rani%20is%20evidently%20proud%3B%20the%20model%20has%20been%20adopted%20by%2016%20countries%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20did%20not%20stop%20there.%20They%20realised%20that%2060%20percent%20of%20infant%20deaths%20are%20due%20to%20sepsis.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20we%20started%20educating%20village%20health%20workers%20%E2%80%98Aarogya%20Doot%E2%80%99%20(Health%20Messengers)%20to%20detect%20and%20treat%20neonatal%20infections.%20This%20brought%20down%20the%20infant%20mortality%20rate%20to%2020%20per%201%2C000.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEducate%20adolescents%20about%20sex%20education%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F346145%2Ftermination-of-pregnancy-act-india-dr-nikhil-datar-case-legal-battle-to-raise-abortion-limit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECriminal%20abortions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dr%20Rani%20highlights%2C%20are%20not%20just%20atrocities%20limited%20to%20tribal%20areas.%20Their%20grip%20extends%20to%20rural%20villages%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CSticks%20and%20local%20herbs%20are%20inserted%20inside%20the%20uterus%20causing%20contractions.%20The%20patient%20is%20forced%20to%20abort%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Rani%20explains.%20Though%20resulting%20in%20the%20desired%20outcome%2C%20the%20sticks%20are%20infective%2C%20causing%20sepsis%20to%20set%20in%20and%20subsequent%20death.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20need%20for%20these%20reductive%20and%20out-of-touch%20procedures%2C%20Dr%20Rani%20highlights.%20%E2%80%9CSince%201971%2C%20India%20has%20legalised%20abortions%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Medic