%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20his%20zero-waste%20startup%2C%20Taruwar%20Agro%2C%20he%20utilises%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F304140%2Fmba-graduate-turns-banana-stem-waste-into-natural-fibre-eco-friendly-handicraft-earns-lakhs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanana%20tree%20waste%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20converting%20it%20into%20banana%20fibre%2C%20which%20eventually%20serves%20as%20a%20raw%20material%20for%20various%20products%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20handicrafts%2C%20yarns%2C%20sanitary%20pads%2C%20and%20banana%20leather.%20By%20turning%20this%20waste%20into%20wealth%2C%20he%20has%20established%20a%20multi-lakh%20venture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20college%20friends%20to%20co-founders%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20his%20engineering%20and%20MBA%2C%20Jagat%20secured%20a%20job%20at%20a%20startup%20that%20focused%20on%20climate%20change%20and%20the%20environment.%20After%20working%20for%20nearly%20a%20year%2C%20he%20received%20various%20job%20offers%20from%20companies%20in%20Tanzania%20and%20Dubai.%20Instead%20of%20accepting%20these%20opportunities%2C%20Jagat%20aspired%20to%20run%20his%20own%20sustainable%20company%20in%20his%20native%20state%20of%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20job%20was%20very%20demanding%20and%20we%20were%20required%20to%20work%20for%2010%20to%2012%20hours.%20I%20would%20often%20discuss%20with%20my%20college%20friends%20Satyam%20Kumar%20and%20Nitish%20Verma%20about%20quitting%20jobs%20to%20build%20something%20meaningful%20of%20our%20own%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20Jagat%20and%20his%20college%20friends%20started%20researching%20various%20issues%20that%20needed%20their%20attention.%20%E2%80%9CThrough%20our%20work%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20put%20Bihar%20on%20the%20world%20map.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20it%20hit%20us%20that%20since%20Hajipur%20is%20known%20for%20its%20banana%20production%2C%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20focus%20on%20banana%20waste%20%E2%80%94%20an%20issue%20that%20all%20of%20us%20grew%20up%20seeing%20on%20our%20fields%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22After%20extracting%20fibre%20from%20banana%20tree%20waste%2C%20the%20startup%20makes%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Ftaruwar-4-1727440526-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-367842%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAfter%20extracting%20fibre%20from%20banana%20tree%20waste%2C%20the%20startup%20makes%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20shape%20their%20dreams%20into%20reality%2C%20the%20trio%20quit%20their%20jobs%20and%20launched%20Taruwar%20Agro%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20innovative%20approach%20focuses%20on%20converting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F310086%2Fmba-graduate-mehul-shroff-sustainable-startup-turns-banana-waste-into-ecofriendly-craft%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanana%20waste%20%3C%2Fa%3Einto%20valuable%20products%2C%20contributing%20to%20environmental%20sustainability%20and%20creating%20economic%20opportunities%20for%20local%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20sources%20banana%20waste%20from%20at%20least%2030%20local%20farmers.%20%E2%80%9CDepending%20on%20the%20size%20of%20the%20tree%2C%20we%20pay%20Rs%205%20and%20Rs%2025%20per%20tree.%20Now%2C%20they%20are%20not%20just%20earning%20by%20selling%20fruit%20but%20also%20tree%20waste.%20Sometimes%2C%20many%20farmers%20do%20not%20accept%20money%2C%20as%20this%20process%20benefits%20them%20in%20clearing%20fields.%20This%20saves%20them%20labour%20costs%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jagat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELeaving%20no%20waste%20behind%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20extracting%20fibre%20from%20banana%20tree%20waste%2C%20the%20startup%20makes%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products%20from%20banana%20fibre%20folders%2C%20yoga%20mats%2C%20baskets%2C%20paintings%2C%20cushion%20covers%2C%20coasters%2C%20and%20more.%20While%20doing%20so%2C%20it%20maintains%20a%20zero-waste%20approach%20in%20all%20its%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20utilises%20the%20leftover%20pulp%20from%20the%20fibre%20extraction%20and%20processes%20it%20into%20high-quality%20vermicompost.%20Furthermore%2C%20Taruwar%20extracts%20banana%20liquid%20from%20the%20pulp%2C%20which%20serves%20as%20a%20natural%20fertiliser%20rich%20in%20micronutrients%20like%20potassium%20and%20iron.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20everything%20in%20the%20process%20is%20turned%20into%20something%20valuable%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20sustainability%20and%20social%20impact%20has%20garnered%20significant%20traction%2C%20with%20an%20annual%20turnover%20of%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20in%20the%20previous%20financial%20year.%20Every%20month%2C%20the%20startup%20utilises%20up%20to%20600%20kg%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F264157%2Fbanana-fibre-earns-lakhs